<HL>
   Italian Wholesale Sales Index
</HL>
<DATE>
06/22/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C6
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   MILAN -- Italy's industrial wholesale sales index in March
rose 5.7% from a year earlier, the state statistical
institute Istat said.
   In February, the index rose 5.3% from a year earlier.
Domestic wholesale sales in March rose 5.3%, and sales to
foreign destinations grew 6.7%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the first three months of this year, wholesale sales
rose 5.9% from the year-earlier period, owing to increases of
5.2% in domestic sales and 8% in foreign sales.
   Sales of capital products to both foreign and domestic
destinations in the first three months grew 10.4% from a year
earlier, and wholesale sales of consumer products rose 8.3%.
Sales of intermediate goods rose 0.9%.
</TEXT>
