<HL>
   Boeing Gets Thai Airways Order
</HL>
<DATE>
06/22/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C19
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST GE BA C.TAC
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<LP>
   SEATTLE -- Boeing Co.'s Commercial Airplane Group said it
received an order from Thai Airways International, the
national carrier of Thailand, for five additional 747-400
widebody jets valued at between $625 million and $735
million.
   The jets will be powered by General Electric Co.'s
CF6-80C2 engines, valued at about $175 million. Thai Airways
has now ordered a total of eight 747-400s, all powered by
CF6-80C2 engines.
</LP>
